1.title: The Thanksgiving Sharing Box
1.plot: When efforts to fix the family float as well as get people to donate to the Thanksgiving Food Drive fail, Nina worries it's because she's a little kid.

2.title: Chelsea's Space Adventure
2.plot: When Chelsea discovers that she can't go to space camp this year, the Star Amigos will help her forget her disappointing news.

3.title: Nina's Baker Boogie
3.plot: Nina really wants to win a dance contest with Papi, but her competitiveness gives Papi two left feet.

4.title: Letter to Santa
4.plot: Nina and friends must deliver a letter from her little brother to Santa Claus before Christmas.

5.title: Santi's Cranky Time
5.plot: Nina and friends try to figure out what Santi wants so he can nap before he throws a tantrum.

6.title: Max Gets Stinky
6.plot: Nina and her friends need to find a sweet-smelling solution to Max's skunky problem.

7.title: Nina's Mysterious Food Truck
7.plot: Nina and her friends try to track down the food truck with the best Arepas in town.

8.title: Lost Alpaca
8.plot: Nina and her friends must find a lost alpaca, which they accidentally let loose from the fair.

9.title: The Bear Trackers
9.plot: When Abuelita gives Nina a mysterious paper filled with random dots, she's told that it holds the key to finding a special bear in their neighborhood. Nina, Carlos, and Chelsea head out on a Bear hunt.

10.title: Biggest Fan
10.plot: When Papi accidentally forgets to buy Mami's soccer game tickets, Nina and her friends save the day.

11.title: The Hand Me Down
11.plot: When Santi decides Lucy the Firefly flashlight is his favorite toy, Nina has a hard time giving up her old 'pal' to her little brother.

12.title: The Sneaky Spider
12.plot: Nina is determined to find and get rid of an ugly house spider that scares her in her bathroom, but she doesn't know enough about the bug to track it down, so Star takes Nina and the Amigos to the bug's world where they come to value the spider it for its contribution to keeping Nina's house safe.

13.title: Sky High Mystery
13.plot: When Chelsea takes a picture with an unidentified flying object in the background, she thinks she's discovered an alien spaceship. But has she?

14.title: Nina and Santi Celebrate Rakhi
14.plot: When Santi is a nuisance and Mr. Kapur explains a South Asian sibling appreciation tradition to her, Nina decides to try Rakhi with her little brother.

15.title: Star Goes Missing
15.plot: Nina's world turns upside down when she loses Star at the street fair.

16.title: Carlos Finds His Voice
16.plot: Right before the big Spring concert, Carlos gets a sore throat and must learn how to sing without using his voice.

17.title: Nina's Superhero Day
17.plot: Nina wants to win a costume contest. But when Papi loses his chance to meet his favorite comic book artist, she finds she'd rather help him meet his hero than win the contest.

18.title: The Best Thank You Gift Ever
18.plot: When Tio Javier does something nice for Nina and her friends, she wants to get him a present. As a result, the Star Amigos get "jobs" around the neighborhood so they can pay for it.

19.title: Nina's New Amigo
19.plot: A trip to the nursing home interrupts Nina's plans to play music with Tío Javier.

20.title: Viva Lucha Libre!
20.plot: After the Amigos watch Luchadors rehearse for a match, Carlos wants to create his own wrestling move. But he plays too rough and has to learn that there's plenty of fun in playing it safe.

21.title: Nina and the Dentist
21.plot: When Nina's scared about her upcoming dentist appointment, Nina enlists the Star Amigos' to help get rid of her fear, so she can be brave for her brother.

22.title: Nina's Nutty Adventure
22.plot: On the day of the bakery's big anniversary celebration, Nina wants to make the bakery, and everything else, safe for Aiden's nut allergy. But Nina takes her campaign too far and ends up making Aiden feel isolated instead.

23.title: Nina's Marionette Show
23.plot: Nina wants to give Abuelita Yolie a special gift: a Mexican marionette show like the one she saw in her youth.

24.title: The New Nina
24.plot: When Nina's favorite cousin Natalia visits from Mexico, Nina feels left out because everyone seems to like Natalia more than her.

25.title: Nina Misses Mami and Papi
25.plot: When Nina's parents take a weekend trip without the kids for the first time ever, Nina can't get over missing them.

26.title: Chelsea's Slam Dunk
26.plot: As the Star Amigos prepare to play Tío Javier in a 3-on-1 basketball rematch, Chelsea hurts her ankle and has a hard time watching from the sidelines.

27.title: Chelsea's Family Day
27.plot: Chelsea learns that there is no such thing as a 'regular' family. There are all kinds of different, equally valid, family models in the world. She can still have fun as a family even if her parents are apart.

28.title: Nina and Abuelita's Special Day
28.plot: Nina tries to have Abuelita all to herself, but realizes that sometimes sharing those you love is a lot more fun.

29.title: Nina Finds a Kitten
29.plot: Nina finds a lost kitten and hopes to keep it for herself.

30.title: Nina's Big Race
30.plot: After Dr. Kapur tells Nina of a charity run to help benefit the local animal shelter, she's very excited, especially when Abuelita and Mami decide to join her. But this "Pet-A-Thon" proves to be a lot tougher than Nina expected.

31.title: The Great Pita Fajita
31.plot: Nina and Hameed team up for their school's Food Fair by making the world's first Pita Fajita, but soliciting too much input from their friends makes them question whether it's as tasty as they originally thought.

32.title: Happy Anniversary Mami and Papi
32.plot: When Mami and Papi are too busy to organize an anniversary dinner, Nina and the Star Amigos take it upon themselves to cook a special meal for them.

33.title: Max Wants to Play
33.plot: When Max the Dog gets hurt, Carlos learns that accidents happen though we do everything we can to avoid them. When an accident happens, you take care of it and then get back to normal as soon as possible.

34.title: The New Clubhouse
34.plot: When a storm wrecks their Clubhouse, Nina and friends don't believe that they can be the Star Amigos without it. But as they search for a new clubhouse, they find that they're still super Star Amigo helpers.

35.title: Nina's Seaside Rescue
35.plot: Nina learns that sometimes rivals need to put aside their differences and work together for the common good.

36.title: Nina in Charge
36.plot: Nina volunteers to be in charge of the kids at a neighborhood BBQ. But when Abuelita offers a piñata for the event, and the kids would rather play with it than do the long list of activities Nina has planned, she has to learn to adjust.

37.title: Nina Live
37.plot: Nina gets the chance to play a song with a famous salsa singer, but first she must get over her fear of playing a new instrument.

38.title: Carlos' Winning Shirt
38.plot: Carlos thinks he can only win the big soccer game if he wears his brother Nico's "winning" t-shirt.

39.title: The Best Ending Ever!
39.plot: When pages from Nina's picture book go missing, the Star Amigos have to come up with a new ending so that Santi will go to sleep.

40.title: Nina the Nature Guide
40.plot: Things don't go as planned on a hiking trip, and Nina must come up with innovative solutions to solve problems.

2.title: Nina's Big Adventure
2.plot: Nina is disappointed that she isn't going on a big adventure like TioJavier - but with a little imagination, she and Abuelita have their own adventure around the block.

3.title: Nina the Nurse
3.plot: Nina is so eager to help Abuelita recover from a cold that she neglects to ask Abuelita what she needs yo feel better.

4.title: Super Nina
4.plot: Nina and Carlos realize they don't need to be superheroes to be amazing - they can be helpful heroes and be just as awesome.

5.title: Nina Wants to Grow
5.plot: Nina wants to grow taller, but eventually she realizes there are positives for her current size.

6.title: Nina's Everything Theatre
6.plot: When Nina discovers a shadow puppet and a variety of costumes in the Everything Store, she and her friends decide to put on a play, but struggle on how to pick the right roles for each friend.

7.title: Nina the Kite Flyer
7.plot: When Carlos accidentally breaks the kite he and Nina made for the Kite Festival, Nina is determined to make a new one with the help of her neighborhood friends.

8.title: Nina's First Sleepover
8.plot: Nina and Star try to be the perfect hosts when Chelsea stays at their house for a sleepover.

9.title: Nina from Space
9.plot: Nina sees her neighborhood in a different way when she and Chelsea pretend to be from another planet.

10.title: Nina Makes Music
10.plot: When Tio Javier is having trouble writing a song, Nina helps inspire him.

11.title: Nina Unplugged
11.plot: Nina sees an opportunity to bring family and friends together, when a blackout causes some concern on the block.

12.title: Nina the Great
12.plot: "Nina the Great" and "Chelsea the Magnificent" nearly let their competitive spirits get in the way of their magic show.

13.title: Nina the Artist
13.plot: Nina tries to paint a picture for a school art project but has such high expectations, she has trouble getting inspired on what to paint. After a frustrating attempt, Nina is disappointed with what she paints, but to her surprise, others seem to like it.

14.title: Nina and the Missing Myna Bird
14.plot: When Dr. Kapur's pet bird escapes, Nina and Star team up with their friends to rescue the music-loving Mynah Bird.

15.title: Nina Delivers
15.plot: Nina goes on an adventure to the post office, she becomes the'best delivery girl ever, discovering how packages are mailed to different parts of the world. Sending something 'from the heart' to family that is far away is the next best thing to being there.

16.title: Nina's Library Hop
16.plot: Determined to uncover the best home possible for her newly rescued frog-pal, Nina disrupts the peace and quiet at the library.

17.title: Nina and Papi Play Baseball
17.plot: When Nina wants to learn how to properly throw a baseball, she asks her dad, a former star high-school pitcher nicknamed El Bola De Fuego, to teach her. But Papi is upset his pitching aim is now WAY off so Nina decides to help her poor dad out.

18.title: Nina the Shadow Chaser
18.plot: While Skye is kid-sitting, Nina and Star watch a scary movie about a shadow monster and their imagination gets away from them.

19.title: Nina's Henna Hijinx
19.plot: When Dr. Kapur, a talented henna artist needs someone to practice on for niece's upcoming wedding, Nina eagerly volunteers. But little did Nina know that waiting for henna to dry is a lot easier said than done.

20.title: Nina's Everything Garden
20.plot: Nina learns to be open to new and different things, when she gets the chance to plant her own garden.

21.title: Nina's Family Museum
21.plot: In "Nina's Family Museum," when Nina, Mami and Abuelita miss out on a day at the museum, Nina decides to create her own mini-museum - of Flores family history! In "Nina Dives In," Nina really wants to learn how to swim, but she and Star are afraid of going into the new - and very big - community pool.

22.title: Nina Dives In
22.plot: In "Nina's Family Museum," when Nina, Mami and Abuelita miss out on a day at the museum, Nina decides to create her own mini-museum - of Flores family history! In "Nina Dives In," Nina really wants to learn how to swim, but she and Star are afraid of going into the new - and very big - community pool.

23.title: Nina Rides a Bike
23.plot: When Nina doesn't want to ride her bike after an accident, Abuelita Yolie, Carlos and Chelsea build her a 'bike school' to get her back on the bike.

24.title: Nina Takes the Cake
24.plot: In "Nina Wants to Grow," Nina wants to grow taller...right now! But eventually she realizes there are good things about being small and that she'll grow when the time is right. In "Nina Takes the Stage," when Nina discovers a Chinese shadow puppet and a variety of costumes in the Everything Store, she and her friends decide to put on a play. But Nina struggles with how to pick the right roles for each friend.

27.title: Nina's Show and Tell
27.plot: When she finds a flower growing in a sidewalk crack, Nina is eager to find a way to savor and share its beauty, and she does -- through photography.

28.title: Nina's Snow Day
28.plot: Nina gives homesick Chelsea a snow party - and learns what winter is like in another part of the world.

29.title: Nina Dances with Nico
29.plot: When Nina has difficulty learning a Mexican folk dance, she discovers through Nico that taking time to feel and enjoy the music is just as important as hearing the music.

30.title: Nina Bakes Bread
30.plot: In "Nina Dances with Nico," Nina wears a traditional Mexican folk dancing costume. In "Nina Bakes Bread," Nina and Chelsea are excited to do some baking in the Flores family bakery.

31.title: Nina's Special Dress
31.plot:

32.title: Nina Hunts for Treasure
32.plot: In "Nina's Special Dress," Nina is so happy that Mami is making her a special dress for school picture day. In "Nina Hunts for Treasure," Mr. Lin is taking Nina, Carlos and Chelsea out to the playground for a treasure hunt.

33.title: Nina Cleans Her Room
33.plot: Abuelita reminds Nina that she has to clean up her room before she can go outside to play with Chelsea. But, Nina gets distracted, finding many fascinating things to do in her room instead.

34.title: Nina's Brother for a Day
34.plot: When Nina's given a school project to report on a sibling, Carlos tells Nina they can share Nico.

35.title: Nina the Detective
35.plot: Detective Nina is on the case -when she discovers a peculiar object (a four-sided boomerang) and attempts to find its owner.

36.title: Nina's Old Oak Tree
36.plot: After weeks with no rain, Nina's favorite tree in the courtyard is drooping. She teams up with her friends to heal the tree and make it feel loved.

37.title: Nina Gets Packing
37.plot: It's Nina's first camping trip and she vows to be the most helpful camper ever by helping the family pack. But all her ideas and deeds are either overlooked or don't work out as the adults scramble to be on the road before dark.

38.title: Nina Camps Out
38.plot: When Nina arrives at the campground she finds everything is very different from her home, and gets a little homesick. But after her family encourages her to try all the wonderful aspects of camping, like hiking, making new discoveries about nature, and cooking over an open fire, Nina soon comes to love living out in the woods.

39.title: Camp Nina
39.plot: Nina had such a great time camping that she now wants to share her experience with her friends,Chelsea and Carlos.But just when they pitch a homemade tent under the old oak, it starts to rain. Her outside camping fun is ruined - or is it.

40.title: Nina's Kickoff
40.plot: Nina is excited when Nico offers to give her, Chelsea and Carlos soccer lessons. But when Carlos feels Nico is getting all the attention and starts acting up, it ruins their practice. It's up to Nina to get the brothers back to being brotherly.

41.title: Nina's Game Day
41.plot: It's a special day as Nina and her friends Chelsea and Carlos compete in fun made-up games. But when Nina doesn't win any of the games, she becomes a bad sport and a sore loser.

42.title: Nina Learns Karate
42.plot: Nina tries her hand at karate and learns that some things require practice, stillness and focus.

43.title: To Mami, Love Nina

45.title: Nina's Color Festival
45.plot: Nina's plan to create a colorful courtyard mural with Chelsea and Carlos goes awry, when her friends have an argument and decide not to take part.

46.title: Nina's Amazing Amigos
46.plot: When Nina, Chelsea and Carlos want to play on the playground at the park,they find themselves face-to-face with a bully.

47.title: Nina and the Yard Sale
47.plot: When the neighborhood has a yard sale, Nina is SHOCKED when she learns Papi is trying to get rid of some of her old toys. And now Nina is DETERMINED to keep them.

48.title: Nina and Papi's Best Day Ever
48.plot: When 'Father's Day' doesn't go quite like Nina had planned, Nina decides it's time for a do-over.

49.title: Nina the Babysitter
49.plot: When a baby comes to visit, Nina and Mami learn that it's not as easy as they thought it would be.

50.title: Nina's Thanksgiving
50.plot: When the oven breaks down in Chelsea's house, she worries that her Thanksgiving will be ruined, but Nina works to save the day.

51.title: Nina's Very Merry Gift
51.plot: Nina makes Christmas tree ornaments for her family and neighbors, but soon discovers that not everyone has a Christmas Tree, or even celebrates the same holiday - and yet they all embrace the season of giving and festive lights.

52.title: Nina Celebrates Chinese New Year
52.plot: Nina is excited when she and her family are invited to the Lins for Chinese New Year celebrations -- featuring a Lion Dance. Nina would love to have an outfit just like Skye has on. But the Lion Dance may be jeopardized when Nina, in her excitement, helps herself to red envelopes that, as it turns out, are meant for the performers.

53.title: Hanukkah Adventure Special
53.plot: A major snow storm is about to hit the city and it's the first night of Hanukkah. When Mrs. Goldstein discovers there is no oil of any kind available due to delayed shipments because of the rare storm, her plans to make her traditional Latkes and jelly donuts are in jeopardy. Enter Jennifer, her can-do, charismatic daughter, home for a visit. She leads Nina, Carlos, and Chelsea in a city-wide search to find vegetable oil for Mrs. Goldstein and olive oil for the Rabbi's Menorah.

55.title: Nina's 4th of July Special
55.plot: Independence Day comes for the United States - and Nina. During the 4th of July Beach Party celebration with family and friends, Nina and Chelsea are determined to ride the big Ferris wheel. Yet after seeing how big it really is, Nina gets cold feet, and keeps putting it off. But when Carlos gets lost in the crowd, Nina discovers that courage can come from the strangest places.

imdb.title: Nina's World
plot: An animated prequel to the Sprout TV network block The Good Night Show, it focuses on the childhood days of Nina, the Latin American host of the block.
